.TH SUPERFETCH 1
.SH NAME
superfetch \- A blazing fast system information tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B superfetch
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B superfetch
is a system information tool written in C that prioritizes extreme performance (executing in ~2 milliseconds). It displays operating system details, hardware information, and package counts alongside your OS logo or custom images via Kitty graphics protocol.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Export the parsed system data as a pure JSON object instead of printing it visually. Ideal for piping into UI widgets (like Waybar or Eww).
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
You can configure \fBsuperfetch\fR by editing \fBconfig.h\fR and running \fBmake\fR to recompile the binary. If you use Pywal, \fBsuperfetch\fR will automatically inherit your terminal color palette from \fI~/.cache/wal/colors\fR. 

To compile without image support and save space, run \fBmake pure\fR.
.SH AUTHOR
Antigravity
